seed_chunks:
Beneath Grinwick’s grin, three powers keep the catacombs “orderly.” The **Candle-Priests of the Patient Wick** bless lanterns, mark safe corridors, and sell comfort; secretly they hoard wrong-note lullabies to bind the Hollow Paths to their altars. The **Rat-Catchers’ Procession** patrols vermin-tunnels and rescues lost children for coin; in truth they smuggle map-fragments and trade names to darkness, betting they can stay ahead of what they feed. Above them all, the **Guild of Varnished Smiles** restores murals and sponsors festivals; covertly they lacquer over doors that shouldn’t exist, erasing routes and witnesses alike. The Priests hire Rat-Catchers as “guides,” the Procession steals priestly hymn-slate, and the Guild blackmails both with painted eyes that remember.

```json
{
  "factions": [
    {
      "name": "Candle-Priests of the Patient Wick",
      "public_front": "Lantern-blessers and corridor-wardens who sell safety, rites, and steady light in the catacombs.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Collect and weaponize wrong-note lullabies to tether the Hollow Paths to their altars and control who is remembered."
    },
    {
      "name": "Rat-Catchers’ Procession",
      "public_front": "Vermin-hunters and tunnel-guides who recover lost folk and keep the lower ways passable—for a price.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Smuggle map-fragments and barter names, favors, and routes to hungry dark things to buy temporary immunity."
    },
    {
      "name": "Guild of Varnished Smiles",
      "public_front": "Mural-restorers and civic patrons who maintain Grinwick’s cheerful face and fund festivals above and below.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Seal or repaint forbidden doors, erase witnesses, and curate what the city is allowed to remember by making walls ‘forget.’"
    }
  ]
}
```

Lanterns across the lower catacombs are guttering blue: the Candle-Priests of the Patient Wick claim “wick-sickness,” but whispers say a stolen hymn-slate is being sung backward at their altars, loosening safe corridors into Hollow Paths. Meanwhile, the Guild of Varnished Smiles has begun an overnight “restoration,” lacquering whole murals shut—sealing exits and trapping pilgrims—after painted eyes allegedly recognized a forbidden door in Liora’s sketches. The Rat-Catchers’ Procession offers escorts at triple price, but some guides are quietly selling clients’ names to the dark to survive the shifting routes.

```json
{
  "events": [
    {
      "name": "The Blue-Guttering Lantern Panic",
      "description": "Lantern-light in the lower catacombs is turning blue and failing as a hymn-slate is rumored to be sung backward at Candle-Priest altars, causing marked safe corridors to fray into Hollow Paths.",
      "tensions": [
        "Pilgrims and workers vanish when ‘safe’ routes fold into nightmare roads",
        "Candle-Priests tighten checkpoints and blame sabotage, risking riots",
        "Whoever controls the hymn-slate can reroute or ‘remember’ travelers at will"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Overnight Lacquer-Seals of the Varnished Smiles",
      "description": "The Guild of Varnished Smiles is rapidly repainting and lacquering murals to erase a newly ‘seen’ forbidden door—possibly linked to Liora’s cartography—locking down entire sections and rewriting what the walls remember.",
      "tensions": [
        "Sealed murals trap people and cut off supplies, provoking desperate tunnel-breaks",
        "Guild agents hunt for sketches and witnesses to eliminate contradictions",
        "Rat-Catchers exploit the chaos, charging more while some barter clients’ names to darkness for protection"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

